==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Corium
<hw>Co"ri*um</hw> <pr>(k?"r?-?m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>corium</ets> leather.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Armor made of
leather, particularly that used by the Romans; used also by English
soldiers till the reign of Edward I.</def>
<rj><au>Fosbroke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Same as
<er>Dermis</er>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The deep layer of mucous
membranes beneath the epithelium.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corival</ent>⟦br⟧
